  "summary": "Jamnagar Refinery\nThe Jamnagar Refinery is the private sector crude oil refinery owned by Reliance Industries in Jamnagar, Gujarat, India. The refinery was commissioned on 14 July 1999 with an installed capacity of 668,000 barrels per day. Its current installed capacity is 1,240,000 barrels per day, and it is currently the largest refinery in the world.",
